title: Solution Architect
description:
Minimum Qualifications:
-  Five (5) years' experience defining high level requirements
-  Five (5) years' experience defining business needs
-  Five (5) years' experience defining data flows 
 Desired Qualifications:
-  Experience with project(s) where software selection was the end product
-  Experience with software selection project(s) for a government agency
-  Experience with Access or other legacy applications
-  Experience with modernization project(s)
-  Experience with business analysis
 Tasks:
-  Interview end users of Commerce Access applications to define and document: 
-  High level business requirements for each application.
-  Data flows in and out of each application.
-  Manual processes associated with each application.
-  Make recommendations on whether each existing application should be replaced by off the shelf software, be replaced by a custom built application, or stay "as is , in order to meet business needs.
-  For each application where replacement with off the shelf software is recommended, identify software option(s) including product name(s), estimated costs, estimated time to implement, and pros/cons of each option if there are multiple options. Where multiple off the shelf software options are identified, provide recommendation as to which option should be chosen.
-  Present findings in writing and verbally to the project team as research/recommendation for each application is completed.
-  Provide knowledge transfer to State staff.
-  Perform other related duties as requested by the State 
 Commerce currently has 23 Access applications that are used to track various aspects of Commerce business. These applications range in functionality from simple to quite complex, and many are critical to business functions. There are also numerous manual paper processes associated with these Access applications. The focus of the Access Modernization project is to replace obsolete and unmaintainable Access applications that no longer meet business needs with modern solutions that meet business needs and are streamlined, efficient, and secure. This will include the automation of manual processes associated with the applications where possible.
 The Solution Architect resource will assess the 23 Access applications (including high-level business requirements, data flows, and any related manual processes) and provide recommendations as to replacement with off the shelf software, replacement with custom built application, or leaving as is.
 The 23 identified applications are in the table below:
 Complaints FMLA Tracking Fuels Monitoring Report (FMR) Grants Insurance Examinations Regional Energy Information Systems (REIS) Utility Data Registration Renewable Energy Production Incentive (REPI) Revenue Yearly Upload RFP Database Self-Insurance Weatherization Assistant Weatherization Assistant - State Reports Module Weatherization Monitoring Issues Log Sircon Reports Distributed Generation /Qualifying Facilities Reports, Financial Exams (AKA Financial Institutions) Actuary Financial Programs Power Clerk Data Viewer Commonline E85 and MidBlend Fuels Petrofund
 Work will be performed off-site/remotely.

title: Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer
description:
Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer
 
 Role:
 
 Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer is responsible for understanding business requirements and delivering high quality technical solutions that empower the Marketing teams to utilize the Marketing Cloud and Email Studio platforms. The communications strategy involves Salesforce integration within a suite of order-related platforms through triggering criteria, logic, prioritization, personalization & messaging.
 This position will work with Marketers, Product and Technical Team members to understand business requirements that drive the analysis and design of quality technical solutions that are aligned with business and IT strategies while complying with the organization's architectural standards.
 
 Job Requirements:
 
-  Ability to work effectively with non-technical personnel
-  Experience with email and/or marketing automation software and integration with databases
-  Knowledge of Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is required
-  Experience working with all Marketing Cloud Builders and Studios, including Mobile Connect, Journey Builder and Automation Studio
-  Develop responsive email templates with HTML and AMPscript
 
 Location: 
 
100% Remot

The top candidate will work closely with partners and end-users. The Solution Architect will align with Outside & Internal Field Sales, Support, and Product Management to support Barracuda’s success!
What you’ll be working on:
 
- The Solution Architect will develop the customer and partner base in an assigned territory and design customer solutions. The Solution Architect will work closely with Sales and other Barracuda teams to help find and close opportunities. The Senior Solution Architect's primary role is to define and implement Barracuda solutions by performing needs assessments, support Proof of Concept evaluations, and Professional Services assignments. The role will require the ability to build and grow technical relationships and knowledge transfer to enable potential clients, in conjunction with both the Barracuda Sales Team and Barracuda Partners.
- Working with Resellers and Barracuda personnel, the Senior Solution Architect will enable customers, support various Sales events, and initial & on-going Sales meetings with Barracuda Sales Reps to position Barracuda solutions with new prospect environments, as well as assisting with on-site evaluations.
- To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to execute on each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability of this role. The top candidate will have strong knowledge and demonstrated success in security solution design and implementation and sales support.
What you bring to the role:
 
- BA / BS preferred.
- 6+ years of Email Security, Networks Security, or Data Protection preferred.
- A demonstrated passion and understanding of Security markets.
- A strong understanding of Security across six threat vectors, email, users, remote users, networks, applications.
- Experience in mid-market and enterprise sales.
- Able to work efficiently and effectively under pressure, while changing and realigning priorities.
- Proven track record of success in a transactional and project-based sales environment.
- Strong understanding of sales processes and methodologies.
- Excellent analytical skills with strong attention to detail.
- Ability to close business while achieving a high level of customer satisfaction.
- Excellent written, verbal and presentation skills.
- Travel involved.
What you’ll get from us:
 
A team where you can voice your opinion, make an impact, and where you and your experience are valued. Internal mobility – there are opportunities for cross training and the ability to attain your next career step within Barracuda. 
- Equity, in the form of non-qualifying options
- High-quality health benefits
- Retirement Plan with employer match
- Career-growth opportunities
- Flexible Time Off and Paid Time Off benefits
- Volunteer opportunities

title: SENIOR MLOPS/DEVOPS ENGINEER
description:
Duties:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Skills:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Technical Skills:
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or Scala.
In-depth knowledge of machine learning frameworks and libraries (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).
Strong understanding of DevOps principles and practices.
Knowledge of infrastructure as code (IaC) tools like Ansible, Terraform, or CloudFormation.
Experience with monitoring and logging tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), or similar.
Understanding of networking, security, and data management principles.
Ability to work with big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Kafka).
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Experience:
5-7 years of relevant experience in roles involving machine learning, software development, DevOps, or a combination thereof.
Experience in progressively challenging roles with demonstrated leadership, project management, and the ability to architect and implement complex systems.
Domain Expertise:
Deep understanding of machine learning concepts, algorithms, and workflows.
Familiarity with various types of machine learning models (e.g., supervised learning, unsupervised learning, reinforcement learning).
Experience with real-world machine learning applications and challenges, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model selection, and evaluation.
Knowledge of industry-specific requirements and compliance standards (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, HITRUST) a plus

title: Senior Vice President of Technology
description:
Job Description:
A property and casualty specialty insurance provider is seeking a Senior Vice President of Technology. The Senior Vice President (SVP) will be responsible for developing and implementing a technology roadmap that delivers on-time solutions to ensure the technology capabilities are aligned with the needs of the organization’s strategic growth plan. The successful leader will eradicate silos, build cross-functional relationships, implement automation for scalable growth, create self-service data capture, and develop streamlined processes to ensure efficiency. As part of the organization’s management team, the SVP will interact with other key leadership members to realize the company’s strategies. Additionally, the company is in the process of implementing the Origami Risk policy administration suite. This is a retained search. 
Responsibilities:
- Provide leadership and vision for the Information Technology (IT) division, including overseeing project roadmaps, strategy, infrastructure, processes, people and budget to enable business priorities.
- Create a culture of accountability and on-time delivery.
- Build strong partnerships with business leaders enterprise wide to innovate service integration and anticipate future requirements.
- Create a streamlined solution that efficiently collects data from multiple sources, both internally as well as from partners, and successfully inputs the information into the data warehouse without compromising integrity for speed.
- Develop cost-effective budgets that best utilize corporate dollars to facilitate efficient capture, storage, processing and dissemination of IT needs to maximize return on investment. 
Requirements:
- 15+ years of IT experience; property and casualty insurance industry experience (preferred)
- Expertise in creating technology roadmaps, organizational design, data warehousing, software applications and methodologies to successfully lead an entire spectrum of technology operations
- Leadership experience in an executive capacity
- Either direct experience with data management and architecture, or has led a team responsible for quality data management
- Bachelor’s degree in information technology or related field (preferred); or an equivalent combination of education and experience

title: Solution Architect
description:
Minimum Qualifications:
-  Five (5) years' experience defining high level requirements
-  Five (5) years' experience defining business needs
-  Five (5) years' experience defining data flows 
 Desired Qualifications:
-  Experience with project(s) where software selection was the end product
-  Experience with software selection project(s) for a government agency
-  Experience with Access or other legacy applications
-  Experience with modernization project(s)
-  Experience with business analysis
 Tasks:
-  Interview end users of Commerce Access applications to define and document: 
-  High level business requirements for each application.
-  Data flows in and out of each application.
-  Manual processes associated with each application.
-  Make recommendations on whether each existing application should be replaced by off the shelf software, be replaced by a custom built application, or stay "as is , in order to meet business needs.
-  For each application where replacement with off the shelf software is recommended, identify software option(s) including product name(s), estimated costs, estimated time to implement, and pros/cons of each option if there are multiple options. Where multiple off the shelf software options are identified, provide recommendation as to which option should be chosen.
-  Present findings in writing and verbally to the project team as research/recommendation for each application is completed.
-  Provide knowledge transfer to State staff.
-  Perform other related duties as requested by the State 
 Commerce currently has 23 Access applications that are used to track various aspects of Commerce business. These applications range in functionality from simple to quite complex, and many are critical to business functions. There are also numerous manual paper processes associated with these Access applications. The focus of the Access Modernization project is to replace obsolete and unmaintainable Access applications that no longer meet business needs with modern solutions that meet business needs and are streamlined, efficient, and secure. This will include the automation of manual processes associated with the applications where possible.
 The Solution Architect resource will assess the 23 Access applications (including high-level business requirements, data flows, and any related manual processes) and provide recommendations as to replacement with off the shelf software, replacement with custom built application, or leaving as is.
 The 23 identified applications are in the table below:
 Complaints FMLA Tracking Fuels Monitoring Report (FMR) Grants Insurance Examinations Regional Energy Information Systems (REIS) Utility Data Registration Renewable Energy Production Incentive (REPI) Revenue Yearly Upload RFP Database Self-Insurance Weatherization Assistant Weatherization Assistant - State Reports Module Weatherization Monitoring Issues Log Sircon Reports Distributed Generation /Qualifying Facilities Reports, Financial Exams (AKA Financial Institutions) Actuary Financial Programs Power Clerk Data Viewer Commonline E85 and MidBlend Fuels Petrofund
 Work will be performed off-site/remotely.

title: Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer
description:
Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer
 
 Role:
 
 Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer is responsible for understanding business requirements and delivering high quality technical solutions that empower the Marketing teams to utilize the Marketing Cloud and Email Studio platforms. The communications strategy involves Salesforce integration within a suite of order-related platforms through triggering criteria, logic, prioritization, personalization & messaging.
 This position will work with Marketers, Product and Technical Team members to understand business requirements that drive the analysis and design of quality technical solutions that are aligned with business and IT strategies while complying with the organization's architectural standards.
 
 Job Requirements:
 
-  Ability to work effectively with non-technical personnel
-  Experience with email and/or marketing automation software and integration with databases
-  Knowledge of Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is required
-  Experience working with all Marketing Cloud Builders and Studios, including Mobile Connect, Journey Builder and Automation Studio
-  Develop responsive email templates with HTML and AMPscript
 
 Location: 
 
100% Remot

The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability of this role. The top candidate will have strong knowledge and demonstrated success in security solution design and implementation and sales support.
What you bring to the role:
 
- BA / BS preferred.
- 6+ years of Email Security, Networks Security, or Data Protection preferred.
- A demonstrated passion and understanding of Security markets.
- A strong understanding of Security across six threat vectors, email, users, remote users, networks, applications.
- Experience in mid-market and enterprise sales.
- Able to work efficiently and effectively under pressure, while changing and realigning priorities.
- Proven track record of success in a transactional and project-based sales environment.
- Strong understanding of sales processes and methodologies.
- Excellent analytical skills with strong attention to detail.
- Ability to close business while achieving a high level of customer satisfaction.
- Excellent written, verbal and presentation skills.

- Retirement Plan with employer match

title: SENIOR MLOPS/DEVOPS ENGINEER
description:
Duties:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Skills:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Technical Skills:
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or Scala.
In-depth knowledge of machine learning frameworks and libraries (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).
Strong understanding of DevOps principles and practices.
Knowledge of infrastructure as code (IaC) tools like Ansible, Terraform, or CloudFormation.
Experience with monitoring and logging tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), or similar.
Understanding of networking, security, and data management principles.
Ability to work with big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Kafka).
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Experience:
5-7 years of relevant experience in roles involving machine learning, software development, DevOps, or a combination thereof.
Experience in progressively challenging roles with demonstrated leadership, project management, and the ability to architect and implement complex systems.
Domain Expertise:
Deep understanding of machine learning concepts, algorithms, and workflows.
Familiarity with various types of machine learning models (e.g., supervised learning, unsupervised learning, reinforcement learning).
Experience with real-world machine learning applications and challenges, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model selection, and evaluation.
Knowledge of industry-specific requirements and compliance standards (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, HITRUST) a plus

title: Senior Vice President of Technology
description:
Job Description:
A property and casualty specialty insurance provider is seeking a Senior Vice President of Technology. The Senior Vice President (SVP) will be responsible for developing and implementing a technology roadmap that delivers on-time solutions to ensure the technology capabilities are aligned with the needs of the organization’s strategic growth plan. The successful leader will eradicate silos, build cross-functional relationships, implement automation for scalable growth, create self-service data capture, and develop streamlined processes to ensure efficiency. As part of the organization’s management team, the SVP will interact with other key leadership members to realize the company’s strategies. Additionally, the company is in the process of implementing the Origami Risk policy administration suite. This is a retained search. 
Responsibilities:
- Provide leadership and vision for the Information Technology (IT) division, including overseeing project roadmaps, strategy, infrastructure, processes, people and budget to enable business priorities.
- Create a culture of accountability and on-time delivery.
- Build strong partnerships with business leaders enterprise wide to innovate service integration and anticipate future requirements.
- Create a streamlined solution that efficiently collects data from multiple sources, both internally as well as from partners, and successfully inputs the information into the data warehouse without compromising integrity for speed.
- Develop cost-effective budgets that best utilize corporate dollars to facilitate efficient capture, storage, processing and dissemination of IT needs to maximize return on investment. 
Requirements:
- 15+ years of IT experience; property and casualty insurance industry experience (preferred)
- Expertise in creating technology roadmaps, organizational design, data warehousing, software applications and methodologies to successfully lead an entire spectrum of technology operations
- Leadership experience in an executive capacity
- Either direct experience with data management and architecture, or has led a team responsible for quality data management
- Bachelor’s degree in information technology or related field (preferred); or an equivalent combination of education and experience

title: Solution Architect
description:
Minimum Qualifications:
-  Five (5) years' experience defining high level requirements
-  Five (5) years' experience defining business needs
-  Five (5) years' experience defining data flows 
 Desired Qualifications:
-  Experience with project(s) where software selection was the end product
-  Experience with software selection project(s) for a government agency
-  Experience with Access or other legacy applications
-  Experience with modernization project(s)
-  Experience with business analysis
 Tasks:
-  Interview end users of Commerce Access applications to define and document: 
-  High level business requirements for each application.
-  Data flows in and out of each application.
-  Manual processes associated with each application.
-  Make recommendations on whether each existing application should be replaced by off the shelf software, be replaced by a custom built application, or stay "as is , in order to meet business needs.
-  For each application where replacement with off the shelf software is recommended, identify software option(s) including product name(s), estimated costs, estimated time to implement, and pros/cons of each option if there are multiple options. Where multiple off the shelf software options are identified, provide recommendation as to which option should be chosen.
-  Present findings in writing and verbally to the project team as research/recommendation for each application is completed.
-  Provide knowledge transfer to State staff.
-  Perform other related duties as requested by the State 
 Commerce currently has 23 Access applications that are used to track various aspects of Commerce business. These applications range in functionality from simple to quite complex, and many are critical to business functions. There are also numerous manual paper processes associated with these Access applications. The focus of the Access Modernization project is to replace obsolete and unmaintainable Access applications that no longer meet business needs with modern solutions that meet business needs and are streamlined, efficient, and secure. This will include the automation of manual processes associated with the applications where possible.
 The Solution Architect resource will assess the 23 Access applications (including high-level business requirements, data flows, and any related manual processes) and provide recommendations as to replacement with off the shelf software, replacement with custom built application, or leaving as is.
 The 23 identified applications are in the table below:
 Complaints FMLA Tracking Fuels Monitoring Report (FMR) Grants Insurance Examinations Regional Energy Information Systems (REIS) Utility Data Registration Renewable Energy Production Incentive (REPI) Revenue Yearly Upload RFP Database Self-Insurance Weatherization Assistant Weatherization Assistant - State Reports Module Weatherization Monitoring Issues Log Sircon Reports Distributed Generation /Qualifying Facilities Reports, Financial Exams (AKA Financial Institutions) Actuary Financial Programs Power Clerk Data Viewer Commonline E85 and MidBlend Fuels Petrofund
 Work will be performed off-site/remotely.

 This position will work with Marketers, Product and Technical Team members to understand business requirements that drive the analysis and design of quality technical solutions that are aligned with business and IT strategies while complying with the organization's architectural standards.
 
 Job Requirements:
 
-  Ability to work effectively with non-technical personnel
-  Experience with email and/or marketing automation software and integration with databases
-  Knowledge of Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is required
-  Experience working with all Marketing Cloud Builders and Studios, including Mobile Connect, Journey Builder and Automation Studio
-  Develop responsive email templates with HTML and AMPscript
 
 Location:

title: SENIOR MLOPS/DEVOPS ENGINEER
description:
Duties:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Skills:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Technical Skills:
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or Scala.
In-depth knowledge of machine learning frameworks and libraries (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).
Strong understanding of DevOps principles and practices.
Knowledge of infrastructure as code (IaC) tools like Ansible, Terraform, or CloudFormation.
Experience with monitoring and logging tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), or similar.
Understanding of networking, security, and data management principles.
Ability to work with big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Kafka).
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Experience:
5-7 years of relevant experience in roles involving machine learning, software development, DevOps, or a combination thereof.
Experience in progressively challenging roles with demonstrated leadership, project management, and the ability to architect and implement complex systems.
Domain Expertise:
Deep understanding of machine learning concepts, algorithms, and workflows.
Familiarity with various types of machine learning models (e.g., supervised learning, unsupervised learning, reinforcement learning).
Experience with real-world machine learning applications and challenges, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model selection, and evaluation.
Knowledge of industry-specific requirements and compliance standards (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, HITRUST) a plus

title: Senior Vice President of Technology
description:
Job Description:
A property and casualty specialty insurance provider is seeking a Senior Vice President of Technology. The Senior Vice President (SVP) will be responsible for developing and implementing a technology roadmap that delivers on-time solutions to ensure the technology capabilities are aligned with the needs of the organization’s strategic growth plan. The successful leader will eradicate silos, build cross-functional relationships, implement automation for scalable growth, create self-service data capture, and develop streamlined processes to ensure efficiency. As part of the organization’s management team, the SVP will interact with other key leadership members to realize the company’s strategies. Additionally, the company is in the process of implementing the Origami Risk policy administration suite. This is a retained search. 
Responsibilities:
- Provide leadership and vision for the Information Technology (IT) division, including overseeing project roadmaps, strategy, infrastructure, processes, people and budget to enable business priorities.
- Create a culture of accountability and on-time delivery.
- Build strong partnerships with business leaders enterprise wide to innovate service integration and anticipate future requirements.
- Create a streamlined solution that efficiently collects data from multiple sources, both internally as well as from partners, and successfully inputs the information into the data warehouse without compromising integrity for speed.
- Develop cost-effective budgets that best utilize corporate dollars to facilitate efficient capture, storage, processing and dissemination of IT needs to maximize return on investment. 
Requirements:
- 15+ years of IT experience; property and casualty insurance industry experience (preferred)
- Expertise in creating technology roadmaps, organizational design, data warehousing, software applications and methodologies to successfully lead an entire spectrum of technology operations
- Leadership experience in an executive capacity
- Either direct experience with data management and architecture, or has led a team responsible for quality data management
- Bachelor’s degree in information technology or related field (preferred); or an equivalent combination of education and experience

title: Solution Architect
description:
Minimum Qualifications:
-  Five (5) years' experience defining high level requirements
-  Five (5) years' experience defining business needs
-  Five (5) years' experience defining data flows 
 Desired Qualifications:
-  Experience with project(s) where software selection was the end product
-  Experience with software selection project(s) for a government agency
-  Experience with Access or other legacy applications
-  Experience with modernization project(s)
-  Experience with business analysis
 Tasks:
-  Interview end users of Commerce Access applications to define and document: 
-  High level business requirements for each application.
-  Data flows in and out of each application.
-  Manual processes associated with each application.
-  Make recommendations on whether each existing application should be replaced by off the shelf software, be replaced by a custom built application, or stay "as is , in order to meet business needs.
-  For each application where replacement with off the shelf software is recommended, identify software option(s) including product name(s), estimated costs, estimated time to implement, and pros/cons of each option if there are multiple options. Where multiple off the shelf software options are identified, provide recommendation as to which option should be chosen.
-  Present findings in writing and verbally to the project team as research/recommendation for each application is completed.
-  Provide knowledge transfer to State staff.
-  Perform other related duties as requested by the State 
 Commerce currently has 23 Access applications that are used to track various aspects of Commerce business. These applications range in functionality from simple to quite complex, and many are critical to business functions. There are also numerous manual paper processes associated with these Access applications. The focus of the Access Modernization project is to replace obsolete and unmaintainable Access applications that no longer meet business needs with modern solutions that meet business needs and are streamlined, efficient, and secure. This will include the automation of manual processes associated with the applications where possible.
 The Solution Architect resource will assess the 23 Access applications (including high-level business requirements, data flows, and any related manual processes) and provide recommendations as to replacement with off the shelf software, replacement with custom built application, or leaving as is.
 The 23 identified applications are in the table below:
 Complaints FMLA Tracking Fuels Monitoring Report (FMR) Grants Insurance Examinations Regional Energy Information Systems (REIS) Utility Data Registration Renewable Energy Production Incentive (REPI) Revenue Yearly Upload RFP Database Self-Insurance Weatherization Assistant Weatherization Assistant - State Reports Module Weatherization Monitoring Issues Log Sircon Reports Distributed Generation /Qualifying Facilities Reports, Financial Exams (AKA Financial Institutions) Actuary Financial Programs Power Clerk Data Viewer Commonline E85 and MidBlend Fuels Petrofund
 Work will be performed off-site/remotely.

 This position will work with Marketers, Product and Technical Team members to understand business requirements that drive the analysis and design of quality technical solutions that are aligned with business and IT strategies while complying with the organization's architectural standards.

-  Ability to work effectively with non-technical personnel
-  Experience with email and/or marketing automation software and integration with databases
-  Knowledge of Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is required
-  Experience working with all Marketing Cloud Builders and Studios, including Mobile Connect, Journey Builder and Automation Studio
-  Develop responsive email templates with HTML and AMPscript
 
 Location:

description:
Job ID (24-426)
 
Come Join Our Passionate Team! At Barracuda, we make the world a safer place. We believe every business deserves access to cloud-enabled, enterprise-grade security solutions that are easy to buy, deploy, and use. We protect email, networks, data and applications with innovative solutions that grow and adapt with our customers’ journey. More than 220,000 organizations worldwide trust Barracuda to protect them — in ways they may not even know they are at risk — so they can focus on taking their business to the next level. 
We know a diverse workforce adds to our collective value and strength as an organization. Barracuda Networks is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to equal employment opportunity and equitable compensation regardless of race, gender, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, or disability.
Envision yourself at Barracuda
 
Barracuda Networks has an open position for a Field Solution Architect. This is a field-based role supporting the Sales efforts with technical management, solution design, enablement and solution implementation. The top candidate will work closely with partners and end-users. The Solution Architect will align with Outside & Internal Field Sales, Support, and Product Management to support Barracuda’s success!
What you’ll be working on:
 
- The Solution Architect will develop the customer and partner base in an assigned territory and design customer solutions. The Solution Architect will work closely with Sales and other Barracuda teams to help find and close opportunities. The Senior Solution Architect's primary role is to define and implement Barracuda solutions by performing needs assessments, support Proof of Concept evaluations, and Professional Services assignments. The role will require the ability to build and grow technical relationships and knowledge transfer to enable potential clients, in conjunction with both the Barracuda Sales Team and Barracuda Partners.
- Working with Resellers and Barracuda personnel, the Senior Solution Architect will enable customers, support various Sales events, and initial & on-going Sales meetings with Barracuda Sales Reps to position Barracuda solutions with new prospect environments, as well as assisting with on-site evaluations.
- To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to execute on each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability of this role. The top candidate will have strong knowledge and demonstrated success in security solution design and implementation and sales support.
What you bring to the role:
 
- BA / BS preferred.
- 6+ years of Email Security, Networks Security, or Data Protection preferred.
- A demonstrated passion and understanding of Security markets.
- A strong understanding of Security across six threat vectors, email, users, remote users, networks, applications.
- Experience in mid-market and enterprise sales.
- Able to work efficiently and effectively under pressure, while changing and realigning priorities.
- Proven track record of success in a transactional and project-based sales environment.
- Strong understanding of sales processes and methodologies.
- Excellent analytical skills with strong attention to detail.
- Ability to close business while achieving a high level of customer satisfaction.
- Excellent written, verbal and presentation skills.
- Travel involved.
What you’ll get from us:
 
A team where you can voice your opinion, make an impact, and where you and your experience are valued. Internal mobility – there are opportunities for cross training and the ability to attain your next career step within Barracuda.

- Retirement Plan with employer match

title: SENIOR MLOPS/DEVOPS ENGINEER
description:
Duties:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Skills:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Technical Skills:
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or Scala.
In-depth knowledge of machine learning frameworks and libraries (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).
Strong understanding of DevOps principles and practices.
Knowledge of infrastructure as code (IaC) tools like Ansible, Terraform, or CloudFormation.
Experience with monitoring and logging tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), or similar.
Understanding of networking, security, and data management principles.
Ability to work with big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Kafka).
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Experience:
5-7 years of relevant experience in roles involving machine learning, software development, DevOps, or a combination thereof.
Experience in progressively challenging roles with demonstrated leadership, project management, and the ability to architect and implement complex systems.
Domain Expertise:
Deep understanding of machine learning concepts, algorithms, and workflows.
Familiarity with various types of machine learning models (e.g., supervised learning, unsupervised learning, reinforcement learning).
Experience with real-world machine learning applications and challenges, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model selection, and evaluation.
Knowledge of industry-specific requirements and compliance standards (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, HITRUST) a plus

title: Senior Vice President of Technology
description:
Job Description:
A property and casualty specialty insurance provider is seeking a Senior Vice President of Technology. The Senior Vice President (SVP) will be responsible for developing and implementing a technology roadmap that delivers on-time solutions to ensure the technology capabilities are aligned with the needs of the organization’s strategic growth plan. The successful leader will eradicate silos, build cross-functional relationships, implement automation for scalable growth, create self-service data capture, and develop streamlined processes to ensure efficiency. As part of the organization’s management team, the SVP will interact with other key leadership members to realize the company’s strategies. Additionally, the company is in the process of implementing the Origami Risk policy administration suite. This is a retained search. 
Responsibilities:
- Provide leadership and vision for the Information Technology (IT) division, including overseeing project roadmaps, strategy, infrastructure, processes, people and budget to enable business priorities.
- Create a culture of accountability and on-time delivery.
- Build strong partnerships with business leaders enterprise wide to innovate service integration and anticipate future requirements.
- Create a streamlined solution that efficiently collects data from multiple sources, both internally as well as from partners, and successfully inputs the information into the data warehouse without compromising integrity for speed.
- Develop cost-effective budgets that best utilize corporate dollars to facilitate efficient capture, storage, processing and dissemination of IT needs to maximize return on investment. 
Requirements:
- 15+ years of IT experience; property and casualty insurance industry experience (preferred)
- Expertise in creating technology roadmaps, organizational design, data warehousing, software applications and methodologies to successfully lead an entire spectrum of technology operations
- Leadership experience in an executive capacity
- Either direct experience with data management and architecture, or has led a team responsible for quality data management
- Bachelor’s degree in information technology or related field (preferred); or an equivalent combination of education and experience

title: Solution Architect
description:
Minimum Qualifications:
-  Five (5) years' experience defining high level requirements
-  Five (5) years' experience defining business needs
-  Five (5) years' experience defining data flows 
 Desired Qualifications:
-  Experience with project(s) where software selection was the end product
-  Experience with software selection project(s) for a government agency
-  Experience with Access or other legacy applications
-  Experience with modernization project(s)
-  Experience with business analysis
 Tasks:
-  Interview end users of Commerce Access applications to define and document: 
-  High level business requirements for each application.
-  Data flows in and out of each application.
-  Manual processes associated with each application.
-  Make recommendations on whether each existing application should be replaced by off the shelf software, be replaced by a custom built application, or stay "as is , in order to meet business needs.
-  For each application where replacement with off the shelf software is recommended, identify software option(s) including product name(s), estimated costs, estimated time to implement, and pros/cons of each option if there are multiple options. Where multiple off the shelf software options are identified, provide recommendation as to which option should be chosen.
-  Present findings in writing and verbally to the project team as research/recommendation for each application is completed.
-  Provide knowledge transfer to State staff.
-  Perform other related duties as requested by the State 
 Commerce currently has 23 Access applications that are used to track various aspects of Commerce business. These applications range in functionality from simple to quite complex, and many are critical to business functions. There are also numerous manual paper processes associated with these Access applications. The focus of the Access Modernization project is to replace obsolete and unmaintainable Access applications that no longer meet business needs with modern solutions that meet business needs and are streamlined, efficient, and secure. This will include the automation of manual processes associated with the applications where possible.
 The Solution Architect resource will assess the 23 Access applications (including high-level business requirements, data flows, and any related manual processes) and provide recommendations as to replacement with off the shelf software, replacement with custom built application, or leaving as is.
 The 23 identified applications are in the table below:
 Complaints FMLA Tracking Fuels Monitoring Report (FMR) Grants Insurance Examinations Regional Energy Information Systems (REIS) Utility Data Registration Renewable Energy Production Incentive (REPI) Revenue Yearly Upload RFP Database Self-Insurance Weatherization Assistant Weatherization Assistant - State Reports Module Weatherization Monitoring Issues Log Sircon Reports Distributed Generation /Qualifying Facilities Reports, Financial Exams (AKA Financial Institutions) Actuary Financial Programs Power Clerk Data Viewer Commonline E85 and MidBlend Fuels Petrofund
 Work will be performed off-site/remotely.

title: Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer
description:
Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer
 
 Role:
 
 Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer is responsible for understanding business requirements and delivering high quality technical solutions that empower the Marketing teams to utilize the Marketing Cloud and Email Studio platforms. The communications strategy involves Salesforce integration within a suite of order-related platforms through triggering criteria, logic, prioritization, personalization & messaging.
 This position will work with Marketers, Product and Technical Team members to understand business requirements that drive the analysis and design of quality technical solutions that are aligned with business and IT strategies while complying with the organization's architectural standards.
 
 Job Requirements:
 
-  Ability to work effectively with non-technical personnel
-  Experience with email and/or marketing automation software and integration with databases
-  Knowledge of Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is required
-  Experience working with all Marketing Cloud Builders and Studios, including Mobile Connect, Journey Builder and Automation Studio
-  Develop responsive email templates with HTML and AMPscript
 
 Location: 
 
100% Remot

title: Solutions Architect
description:
Job ID (24-426)
 
Come Join Our Passionate Team! At Barracuda, we make the world a safer place. We believe every business deserves access to cloud-enabled, enterprise-grade security solutions that are easy to buy, deploy, and use. We protect email, networks, data and applications with innovative solutions that grow and adapt with our customers’ journey. More than 220,000 organizations worldwide trust Barracuda to protect them — in ways they may not even know they are at risk — so they can focus on taking their business to the next level. 
We know a diverse workforce adds to our collective value and strength as an organization. Barracuda Networks is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to equal employment opportunity and equitable compensation regardless of race, gender, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, or disability.
Envision yourself at Barracuda
 
Barracuda Networks has an open position for a Field Solution Architect. This is a field-based role supporting the Sales efforts with technical management, solution design, enablement and solution implementation. The top candidate will work closely with partners and end-users. The Solution Architect will align with Outside & Internal Field Sales, Support, and Product Management to support Barracuda’s success!
What you’ll be working on:
 
- The Solution Architect will develop the customer and partner base in an assigned territory and design customer solutions. The Solution Architect will work closely with Sales and other Barracuda teams to help find and close opportunities. The Senior Solution Architect's primary role is to define and implement Barracuda solutions by performing needs assessments, support Proof of Concept evaluations, and Professional Services assignments. The role will require the ability to build and grow technical relationships and knowledge transfer to enable potential clients, in conjunction with both the Barracuda Sales Team and Barracuda Partners.
- Working with Resellers and Barracuda personnel, the Senior Solution Architect will enable customers, support various Sales events, and initial & on-going Sales meetings with Barracuda Sales Reps to position Barracuda solutions with new prospect environments, as well as assisting with on-site evaluations.
- To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to execute on each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability of this role. The top candidate will have strong knowledge and demonstrated success in security solution design and implementation and sales support.
What you bring to the role:
 
- BA / BS preferred.
- 6+ years of Email Security, Networks Security, or Data Protection preferred.
- A demonstrated passion and understanding of Security markets.
- A strong understanding of Security across six threat vectors, email, users, remote users, networks, applications.
- Experience in mid-market and enterprise sales.
- Able to work efficiently and effectively under pressure, while changing and realigning priorities.
- Proven track record of success in a transactional and project-based sales environment.
- Strong understanding of sales processes and methodologies.
- Excellent analytical skills with strong attention to detail.
- Ability to close business while achieving a high level of customer satisfaction.
- Excellent written, verbal and presentation skills.
- Travel involved.
What you’ll get from us:
 
A team where you can voice your opinion, make an impact, and where you and your experience are valued. Internal mobility – there are opportunities for cross training and the ability to attain your next career step within Barracuda. 
- Equity, in the form of non-qualifying options
- High-quality health benefits
- Retirement Plan with employer match
- Career-growth opportunities
- Flexible Time Off and Paid Time Off benefits
- Volunteer opportunities

title: SENIOR MLOPS/DEVOPS ENGINEER
description:
Duties:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Skills:
Build, test and maintain the infrastructure and tools to facilitate the consistent and automated AI software solution development and release process.
Design, build and maintain the CI/CD pipeline that automates data collection, data analysis, experimentation, model training, model serving and monitoring in production. Achieve continuous delivery of AI software solution and updates to production at scale.
Provide direction to more junior engineers.
Collaborate with data scientists, engineers, product teams and other key stakeholders.
Actively seek ways to improve software development and operation process.
Technical Skills:
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or Scala.
In-depth knowledge of machine learning frameworks and libraries (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn).
Strong understanding of DevOps principles and practices.
Knowledge of infrastructure as code (IaC) tools like Ansible, Terraform, or CloudFormation.
Experience with monitoring and logging tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana), or similar.
Understanding of networking, security, and data management principles.
Ability to work with big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Kafka).
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Experience:
5-7 years of relevant experience in roles involving machine learning, software development, DevOps, or a combination thereof.
Experience in progressively challenging roles with demonstrated leadership, project management, and the ability to architect and implement complex systems.
Domain Expertise:
Deep understanding of machine learning concepts, algorithms, and workflows.
Familiarity with various types of machine learning models (e.g., supervised learning, unsupervised learning, reinforcement learning).
Experience with real-world machine learning applications and challenges, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model selection, and evaluation.
Knowledge of industry-specific requirements and compliance standards (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, HITRUST) a plus

title: Senior Vice President of Technology
description:
Job Description:
A property and casualty specialty insurance provider is seeking a Senior Vice President of Technology. The Senior Vice President (SVP) will be responsible for developing and implementing a technology roadmap that delivers on-time solutions to ensure the technology capabilities are aligned with the needs of the organization’s strategic growth plan. The successful leader will eradicate silos, build cross-functional relationships, implement automation for scalable growth, create self-service data capture, and develop streamlined processes to ensure efficiency. As part of the organization’s management team, the SVP will interact with other key leadership members to realize the company’s strategies. Additionally, the company is in the process of implementing the Origami Risk policy administration suite. This is a retained search. 
Responsibilities:
- Provide leadership and vision for the Information Technology (IT) division, including overseeing project roadmaps, strategy, infrastructure, processes, people and budget to enable business priorities.
- Create a culture of accountability and on-time delivery.
- Build strong partnerships with business leaders enterprise wide to innovate service integration and anticipate future requirements.
- Create a streamlined solution that efficiently collects data from multiple sources, both internally as well as from partners, and successfully inputs the information into the data warehouse without compromising integrity for speed.
- Develop cost-effective budgets that best utilize corporate dollars to facilitate efficient capture, storage, processing and dissemination of IT needs to maximize return on investment. 
Requirements:
- 15+ years of IT experience; property and casualty insurance industry experience (preferred)
- Expertise in creating technology roadmaps, organizational design, data warehousing, software applications and methodologies to successfully lead an entire spectrum of technology operations
- Leadership experience in an executive capacity
- Either direct experience with data management and architecture, or has led a team responsible for quality data management
- Bachelor’s degree in information technology or related field (preferred); or an equivalent combination of education and experience

title: Solution Architect
description:
Minimum Qualifications:
-  Five (5) years' experience defining high level requirements
-  Five (5) years' experience defining business needs
-  Five (5) years' experience defining data flows 
 Desired Qualifications:
-  Experience with project(s) where software selection was the end product
-  Experience with software selection project(s) for a government agency
-  Experience with Access or other legacy applications
-  Experience with modernization project(s)
-  Experience with business analysis
 Tasks:
-  Interview end users of Commerce Access applications to define and document: 
-  High level business requirements for each application.
-  Data flows in and out of each application.
-  Manual processes associated with each application.
-  Make recommendations on whether each existing application should be replaced by off the shelf software, be replaced by a custom built application, or stay "as is , in order to meet business needs.
-  For each application where replacement with off the shelf software is recommended, identify software option(s) including product name(s), estimated costs, estimated time to implement, and pros/cons of each option if there are multiple options. Where multiple off the shelf software options are identified, provide recommendation as to which option should be chosen.
-  Present findings in writing and verbally to the project team as research/recommendation for each application is completed.
-  Provide knowledge transfer to State staff.
-  Perform other related duties as requested by the State 
 Commerce currently has 23 Access applications that are used to track various aspects of Commerce business. These applications range in functionality from simple to quite complex, and many are critical to business functions. There are also numerous manual paper processes associated with these Access applications. The focus of the Access Modernization project is to replace obsolete and unmaintainable Access applications that no longer meet business needs with modern solutions that meet business needs and are streamlined, efficient, and secure. This will include the automation of manual processes associated with the applications where possible.
 The Solution Architect resource will assess the 23 Access applications (including high-level business requirements, data flows, and any related manual processes) and provide recommendations as to replacement with off the shelf software, replacement with custom built application, or leaving as is.
 The 23 identified applications are in the table below:
 Complaints FMLA Tracking Fuels Monitoring Report (FMR) Grants Insurance Examinations Regional Energy Information Systems (REIS) Utility Data Registration Renewable Energy Production Incentive (REPI) Revenue Yearly Upload RFP Database Self-Insurance Weatherization Assistant Weatherization Assistant - State Reports Module Weatherization Monitoring Issues Log Sircon Reports Distributed Generation /Qualifying Facilities Reports, Financial Exams (AKA Financial Institutions) Actuary Financial Programs Power Clerk Data Viewer Commonline E85 and MidBlend Fuels Petrofund
 Work will be performed off-site/remotely.

 This position will work with Marketers, Product and Technical Team members to understand business requirements that drive the analysis and design of quality technical solutions that are aligned with business and IT strategies while complying with the organization's architectural standards.

-  Experience with email and/or marketing automation software and integration with databases
-  Knowledge of Salesforce Marketing Cloud (SFMC) is required
-  Experience working with all Marketing Cloud Builders and Studios, including Mobile Connect, Journey Builder and Automation Studio
-  Develop responsive email templates with HTML and AMPscript
 
 Location:

title: Solutions Architect
description:
Job ID (24-426)
 
Come Join Our Passionate Team! At Barracuda, we make the world a safer place. We believe every business deserves access to cloud-enabled, enterprise-grade security solutions that are easy to buy, deploy, and use. We protect email, networks, data and applications with innovative solutions that grow and adapt with our customers’ journey. More than 220,000 organizations worldwide trust Barracuda to protect them — in ways they may not even know they are at risk — so they can focus on taking their business to the next level. 
We know a diverse workforce adds to our collective value and strength as an organization. Barracuda Networks is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to equal employment opportunity and equitable compensation regardless of race, gender, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin, or disability.
Envision yourself at Barracuda
 
Barracuda Networks has an open position for a Field Solution Architect. This is a field-based role supporting the Sales efforts with technical management, solution design, enablement and solution implementation. The top candidate will work closely with partners and end-users. The Solution Architect will align with Outside & Internal Field Sales, Support, and Product Management to support Barracuda’s success!
What you’ll be working on:
 
- The Solution Architect will develop the customer and partner base in an assigned territory and design customer solutions. The Solution Architect will work closely with Sales and other Barracuda teams to help find and close opportunities. The Senior Solution Architect's primary role is to define and implement Barracuda solutions by performing needs assessments, support Proof of Concept evaluations, and Professional Services assignments. The role will require the ability to build and grow technical relationships and knowledge transfer to enable potential clients, in conjunction with both the Barracuda Sales Team and Barracuda Partners.
- Working with Resellers and Barracuda personnel, the Senior Solution Architect will enable customers, support various Sales events, and initial & on-going Sales meetings with Barracuda Sales Reps to position Barracuda solutions with new prospect environments, as well as assisting with on-site evaluations.
- To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to execute on each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability of this role. The top candidate will have strong knowledge and demonstrated success in security solution design and implementation and sales support.
What you bring to the role:
 
- BA / BS preferred.
- 6+ years of Email Security, Networks Security, or Data Protection preferred.
- A demonstrated passion and understanding of Security markets.
- A strong understanding of Security across six threat vectors, email, users, remote users, networks, applications.
- Experience in mid-market and enterprise sales.
- Able to work efficiently and effectively under pressure, while changing and realigning priorities.
- Proven track record of success in a transactional and project-based sales environment.
- Strong understanding of sales processes and methodologies.
- Excellent analytical skills with strong attention to detail.
- Ability to close business while achieving a high level of customer satisfaction.
- Excellent written, verbal and presentation skills.
- Travel involved.
What you’ll get from us:
 
A team where you can voice your opinion, make an impact, and where you and your experience are valued. Internal mobility – there are opportunities for cross training and the ability to attain your next career step within Barracuda. 
- Equity, in the form of non-qualifying options
- High-quality health benefits
- Retirement Plan with employer match
- Career-growth opportunities
- Flexible Time Off and Paid Time Off benefits
- Volunteer opportunities
 
#LI-Remote
